
===================================
📌 1. Finglish Version (Persian Latin Script)
===================================

📖 **Tashrih:**
    Dastoor `hex2hcd` baraye tabdil kardan file-haye hexadecimal be format HCD (Hewlett-Packard Configuration Database) estefade mishavad. In dastoor be shoma komak mikonad ta etela'at ra az format hexadecimal be format HP be asani taghir dahid.

⚙️ **Gozine-ha:**
    🔹 `hex2hcd <file.hex> <file.hcd>`  --> 🔄 Tabdil file HEX be file HCD.
    🔹 `hex2hcd -v`  --> 📢 Namayesh version dastoor.
    🔹 `hex2hcd -h`  --> ❓ Namayesh komak va rahnamayi dastoor.

🛠 **Mesal-ha:**

    $ hex2hcd input.hex output.hcd

    🔹 Tabdil file `input.hex` be file `output.hcd`.

    $ hex2hcd -v

    🔹 Namayesh version dastoor `hex2hcd`.

✅ **Mesal sade:**

    $ hex2hcd firmware.hex firmware.hcd

    🔹 File `firmware.hex` be file `firmware.hcd` tabdil mishavad, ke mitavanad baraye update kardan dastgah HP estefade shavad.

===================================
📌 2. English Version
===================================

📖 **Description:**
    The `hex2hcd` command is used to convert hexadecimal files to the HCD (Hewlett-Packard Configuration Database) format. This tool helps you easily transform information from a hexadecimal format to an HP configuration file.

⚙️ **Options:**
    🔹 `hex2hcd <file.hex> <file.hcd>`  --> 🔄 Converts a HEX file to an HCD file.
    🔹 `hex2hcd -v`  --> 📢 Displays the version of the command.
    🔹 `hex2hcd -h`  --> ❓ Shows help and usage instructions for the command.

🛠 **Examples:**

    $ hex2hcd input.hex output.hcd

    🔹 Converts the file `input.hex` to the file `output.hcd`.

    $ hex2hcd -v

    🔹 Displays the version of the `hex2hcd` command.

✅ **Simple Example:**

    $ hex2hcd firmware.hex firmware.hcd

    🔹 The file `firmware.hex` is converted to `firmware.hcd`, which can then be used to update an HP device.
